123 template<class T>
124 T Check(T result)
125 {
126  OCI_Error *err = OCI_GetLastError();
127 
128  if (err)
129  {
130  throw Exception(err);
131  }
132 
133  return result;
134 }
135 
136 inline ostring MakeString(const otext *result, int size)
137 {
138  return result ? (size >= 0 ? ostring(result, result + size) : ostring(result)) : ostring();
139 }
140 
141 inline Raw MakeRaw(void *result, unsigned int size)
142 {
143  unsigned char *ptr = static_cast<unsigned char *>(result);
144 
145  return (ptr && size > 0 ? Raw(ptr, ptr + size) : Raw());
146 }
147 
148 template<class S, class C>
149 void ConverString(S &dest, const C *src, size_t length)
150 {
151  size_t i = 0;
152 
153  dest.clear();
154 
155  if (src)
156  {
157  dest.resize(length);
158 
159  while (i < length)
160  {
161  dest[i] = static_cast<typename S::value_type>(src[i]);
162 
163  ++i;
164  }
165  }
166 }

416 template<class T>
417 HandleHolder<T>::HandleHolder(const HandleHolder &other) : _smartHandle(nullptr)

423 HandleHolder<T>::~HandleHolder()
424 {
425  Release();
426 }

429 HandleHolder<T>& HandleHolder<T>::operator = (const HandleHolder<T> &other)
430 {
431  Acquire(other, nullptr, nullptr, other._smartHandle ? other._smartHandle->GetParent() : nullptr);
432  return *this;

454 HandleHolder<T>::operator bool()

466 Handle * HandleHolder<T>::GetHandle() const
467 {
468  return static_cast<Handle *>(_smartHandle);

470 
471 template<class T>
472 void HandleHolder<T>::Acquire(T handle, HandleFreeFunc handleFreefunc, SmartHandleFreeNotifyFunc freeNotifyFunc, Handle *parent)
473 {
474  Release();
475 
476  if (handle)
477  {
478  _smartHandle = Environment::GetSmartHandle<SmartHandle*>(handle);
479 
480  if (!_smartHandle)
481  {
482  _smartHandle = new SmartHandle(this, handle, handleFreefunc, freeNotifyFunc, parent);
483  }
484  else
485  {
486  _smartHandle->Acquire(this);
487  }
488  }
489 }
490 
491 template<class T>
492 void HandleHolder<T>::Acquire(HandleHolder<T> &other)
493 {
494  if (&other != this && _smartHandle != other._smartHandle)
495  {
496  Release();
497 
498  if (other._smartHandle)
499  {
500  other._smartHandle->Acquire(this);
501  _smartHandle = other._smartHandle;
502  }
503  }
504 }
505 
506 template<class T>
507 void HandleHolder<T>::Release()
508 {
509  if (_smartHandle)
510  {
511  _smartHandle->Release(this);
512  }
513 
514  _smartHandle = nullptr;
515 }
516 
517 inline Locker::Locker() : _mutex(nullptr)
518 {
519  SetAccessMode(false);
520 }
521 
522 inline Locker::~Locker()
523 {
524  SetAccessMode(false);
525 }
526 
527 inline void Locker::SetAccessMode(bool threaded)
528 {
529  if (threaded && !_mutex)
530  {
531  _mutex = Mutex::Create();
532  }
533  else if (!threaded && _mutex)
534  {
535  Mutex::Destroy(_mutex);
536  _mutex = nullptr;
537  }
538 }
539 
540 inline void Locker::Lock() const
541 {
542  if (_mutex)
543  {
544  Mutex::Acquire(_mutex);
545  }
546 }
547 
548 inline void Locker::Unlock() const
549 {
550  if (_mutex)
551  {
552  Mutex::Release(_mutex);
553  }
554 }

587 template<class K, class V>
588 ConcurrentMap<K, V>::ConcurrentMap()
589 {
590 
591 }
592 
593 template<class K, class V>
594 ConcurrentMap<K, V>::~ConcurrentMap()
595 {
596  Clear();
597 }
598 
599 template<class K, class V>
600 void ConcurrentMap<K, V>::Remove(K key)
601 {
602  Lock();
603  _map.erase(key);
604  Unlock();
605 }
606 
607 template<class K, class V>
608 V ConcurrentMap<K, V>::Get(K key)
609 {
610  V value = 0;
611 
612  Lock();
613  typename std::map< K, V >::const_iterator it = _map.find(key);
614  if (it != _map.end())
615  {
616  value = it->second;
617  }
618  Unlock();
619 
620  return value;
621 }
622 
623 template<class K, class V>
624 void ConcurrentMap<K, V>::Set(K key, V value)
625 {
626  Lock();
627  _map[key] = value;
628  Unlock();
629 }
630 
631 template<class K, class V>
632 void ConcurrentMap<K, V>::Clear()
633 {
634  Lock();
635  _map.clear();
636  Unlock();
637 }
638 
639 template<class K, class V>
640 size_t ConcurrentMap<K, V>::GetSize()
641 {
642  Lock();
643  size_t size = _map.size();
644  Unlock();
645 
646  return size;
647 }

658  Clear();

661 template<class T>
662 void ConcurrentList<T>::Add(T value)
663 {
664  Lock();
665  _list.push_back(value);
666  Unlock();
667 }
668 
669 template<class T>
670 void ConcurrentList<T>::Remove(T value)
671 {
672  Lock();
673  _list.remove(value);
674  Unlock();
675 }
676 
677 template<class T>
678 void ConcurrentList<T>::Clear()
679 {
680  Lock();
681  _list.clear();
682  Unlock();
683 }
684 
685 template<class T>
686 size_t ConcurrentList<T>::GetSize()
687 {
688  Lock();
689  size_t size = _list.size();
690  Unlock();

693 }
694 
695 template<class T>
696 bool ConcurrentList<T>::Exists(const T &value)
697 {
698  Lock();
699 
700  bool res = std::find(_list.begin(), _list.end(), value) != _list.end();
701 
702  Unlock();
703 
704  return res;
705 }
706 
707 template<class T>
708 template<class P>
709 bool ConcurrentList<T>::FindIf(P predicate, T &value)
710 {
711  bool res = false;
712 
713  Lock();
714 
715  typename std::list<T>::iterator it = std::find_if(_list.begin(), _list.end(), predicate);
716 
717  if (it != _list.end())
718  {
719  value = *it;
720  res = true;
721  }
722 
723  Unlock();
724 
725  return res;
726 }
727 
728 template<class T>
729 template<class A>
730 void ConcurrentList<T>::ForEach(A action)
731 {
732  Lock();
733 
734  std::for_each(_list.begin(), _list.end(), action);
735 
736  Unlock();
737 }

739 template<class T>
740 HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::SmartHandle
741 (
742  HandleHolder *holder, T handle, HandleFreeFunc handleFreefunc,
743  SmartHandleFreeNotifyFunc freeNotifyFunc, Handle *parent
744 )
745  : _holders(), _children(), _locker(), _handle(handle), _handleFreeFunc(handleFreefunc),
746  _freeNotifyFunc(freeNotifyFunc), _parent(parent), _extraInfo(nullptr)
747 {
748  _locker.SetAccessMode((Environment::GetMode() & Environment::Threaded) == Environment::Threaded);
749 
750  _holders.SetLocker(&_locker);
751  _children.SetLocker(&_locker);
752 
753  Environment::SetSmartHandle<SmartHandle*>(handle, this);
754 
755  Acquire(holder);
756 
757  if (_parent && _handle)
758  {
759  _parent->GetChildren().Add(this);
760  }
761 }
762 
763 template<class T>
764 HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::~SmartHandle()
765 {
766  boolean ret = TRUE;
767  boolean chk = FALSE;
768 
769  if (_parent && _handle)
770  {
771  _parent->GetChildren().Remove(this);
772  }
773 
774  _children.ForEach(DeleteHandle);
775  _children.Clear();
776 
777  _holders.SetLocker(nullptr);
778  _children.SetLocker(nullptr);
779 
780  Environment::SetSmartHandle<SmartHandle*>(_handle, nullptr);
781 
782  if (_freeNotifyFunc)
783  {
784  _freeNotifyFunc(this);
785  }
786 
787  if (_handleFreeFunc && _handle)
788  {
789  ret = _handleFreeFunc(_handle);
790  chk = TRUE;
791  }
792 
793  if (chk)
794  {
795  Check(ret);
796  }
797 }
798 
799 template<class T>
800 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::DeleteHandle(Handle *handle)
801 {
802  if (handle)
803  {
804  handle->DetachFromParent();
805  handle->DetachFromHolders();
806 
807  delete handle;
808  }
809 }
810 
811 template<class T>
812 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::ResetHolder(HandleHolder *holder)
813 {
814  if (holder)
815  {
816  holder->_smartHandle = 0;
817  }
818 }
819 
820 template<class T>
821 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::Acquire(HandleHolder *holder)
822 {
823  _holders.Add(holder);
824 }
825 
826 template<class T>
827 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::Release(HandleHolder *holder)
828 {
829  _holders.Remove(holder);
830 
831  if (_holders.GetSize() == 0)
832  {
833  delete this;
834  }
835 
836  holder->_smartHandle = nullptr;
837 }
838 
839 template<class T>
840 T HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::GetHandle() const
841 {
842  return _handle;
843 }
844 
845 template<class T>
846 Handle * HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::GetParent() const
847 {
848  return _parent;
849 }
850 
851 template<class T>
852 AnyPointer HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::GetExtraInfos() const
853 {
854  return _extraInfo;
855 }
856 
857 template<class T>
858 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::SetExtraInfos(AnyPointer extraInfo)
859 {
860  _extraInfo = extraInfo;
861 }
862 
863 template<class T>
864 ConcurrentList<Handle *> & HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::GetChildren()
865 {
866  return _children;
867 }
868 
869 template<class T>
870 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::DetachFromHolders()
871 {
872  _holders.ForEach(ResetHolder);
873  _holders.Clear();
874 }
875 
876 template<class T>
877 void HandleHolder<T>::SmartHandle::DetachFromParent()
878 {
879  _parent = nullptr;
880 }

882 /* --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- *
883  * Exception
884  * --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
885 
886 inline Exception::Exception()
887  : _what(),
888  _pStatement(nullptr),
889  _pConnnection(nullptr),
890  _row(0),
891  _type(static_cast<ExceptionType::Type>(0)),
892  _errLib(0),
893  _errOracle(0)
894 {
895

903 inline Exception::Exception(OCI_Error *err)
904  : _what(),
905  _pStatement(OCI_ErrorGetStatement(err)),
906  _pConnnection(OCI_ErrorGetConnection(err)),
907  _row(OCI_ErrorGetRow(err)),
908  _type(static_cast<ExceptionType::Type>(OCI_ErrorGetType(err))),
909  _errLib(OCI_ErrorGetInternalCode(err)),
910  _errOracle(OCI_ErrorGetOCICode(err))
911 {
912  const otext *str = OCI_ErrorGetString(err);
913 
914  if (str)
915  {
916  ConverString(_what, str, ostrlen(str));
917  }
918 }
919 
920 inline const char * Exception::what() const throw()
921 {
922  return _what.c_str();
923 }

925 inline ostring Exception::GetMessage() const
926 {
927  ostring message;
928 
929 #ifdef OCI_CHARSET_WIDE
930 
931  ConverString(message, _what.c_str(), _what.size());
932 
933 #else
934 
935  message = _what;
936 
937 #endif
938 
939  return message;
940 }

1085 inline void Environment::SetHAHandler(HAHandlerProc handler)
1086 {
1087  Check(OCI_SetHAHandler(static_cast<POCI_HA_HANDLER>(handler != nullptr ? Environment::HAHandler : nullptr)));
1088

1091 
1092 inline void Environment::HAHandler(OCI_Connection *pConnection, unsigned int source, unsigned int event, OCI_Timestamp *pTimestamp)
1093 {
1094  HAHandlerProc handler = Environment::GetUserCallback<HAHandlerProc>(GetEnvironmentHandle());
1095 
1096  if (handler)
1097  {
1098  Connection connection(pConnection, nullptr);
1099  Timestamp timestamp(pTimestamp, connection.GetHandle());
1100 
1101  handler(connection,
1102  HAEventSource(static_cast<HAEventSource::Type>(source)),
1103  HAEventType (static_cast<HAEventType::Type> (event)),
1104  timestamp);
1105  }
1106 }
1107 
1108 inline unsigned int Environment::TAFHandler(OCI_Connection *pConnection, unsigned int type, unsigned int event)
1109 {
1110  unsigned int res = OCI_FOC_OK;
1111 
1112  Connection::TAFHandlerProc handler = Environment::GetUserCallback<Connection::TAFHandlerProc>(Check(pConnection));
1113 
1114  if (handler)
1115  {
1116  Connection connection(pConnection, nullptr);
1117 
1118  res = handler(connection,
1119  Connection::FailoverRequest( static_cast<Connection::FailoverRequest::Type> (type)),
1120  Connection::FailoverEvent ( static_cast<Connection::FailoverEvent::Type> (event)));
1121  }
1122 
1123  return res;
1124 }
1125 
1126 inline void Environment::NotifyHandler(OCI_Event *pEvent)
1127 {
1128  Subscription::NotifyHandlerProc handler = Environment::GetUserCallback<Subscription::NotifyHandlerProc>((Check(OCI_EventGetSubscription(pEvent))));
1129 
1130  if (handler)
1131  {
1132  Event evt(pEvent);
1133  handler(evt);
1134  }
1135 }
1136 
1137 inline void Environment::NotifyHandlerAQ(OCI_Dequeue *pDequeue)
1138 {
1139  Dequeue::NotifyAQHandlerProc handler = Environment::GetUserCallback<Dequeue::NotifyAQHandlerProc>(Check(pDequeue));
1140 
1141  if (handler)
1142  {
1143  Dequeue dequeue(pDequeue);
1144  handler(dequeue);
1145  }
1146 }

1148 template<class T>
1149 T Environment::GetUserCallback(AnyPointer ptr)
1150 {
1151  return reinterpret_cast<T>(GetInstance()._callbacks.Get(ptr));
1152 }
1153 
1154 template<class T>
1155 void Environment::SetUserCallback(AnyPointer ptr, T callback)
1156 {
1157  if (callback)
1158  {
1159  GetInstance()._callbacks.Set(ptr, reinterpret_cast<CallbackPointer>(callback));
1160  }
1161  else
1162  {
1163  GetInstance()._callbacks.Remove(ptr);
1164  }
1165 }
1166 
1167 template<class T>
1168 void Environment::SetSmartHandle(AnyPointer ptr, T handle)
1169 {
1170  if (handle)
1171  {
1172  GetInstance()._handles.Set(ptr, handle);
1173  }
1174  else
1175  {
1176  GetInstance()._handles.Remove(ptr);
1177  }
1178 }
1179 
1180 template<class T>
1181 T Environment::GetSmartHandle(AnyPointer ptr)
1182 {
1183  return dynamic_cast<T>(GetInstance()._handles.Get(ptr));
1184 }

1198 inline Environment::Environment() : _locker(), _handle(), _handles(), _callbacks(), _mode(), _initialized(false)
1199 {
1200 
1201 }
1202 
1203 inline void Environment::SelfInitialize(EnvironmentFlags mode, const ostring& libpath)
1204 {
1205  _mode = mode;
1206 
1207  Check(OCI_Initialize(nullptr, libpath.c_str(), _mode.GetValues() | OCI_ENV_CONTEXT));
1208 
1209  _initialized = true;
1210 
1211  _locker.SetAccessMode((_mode & Environment::Threaded) == Environment::Threaded);
1212 
1213  _callbacks.SetLocker(&_locker);
1214  _handles.SetLocker(&_locker);
1215 
1216  _handle.Acquire(const_cast<AnyPointer>(Check(OCI_HandleGetEnvironment())), nullptr, nullptr, nullptr);
1217 }
1218 
1219 inline void Environment::SelfCleanup()
1220 {
1221  _locker.SetAccessMode(false);
1222 
1223  _callbacks.SetLocker(nullptr);
1224  _handles.SetLocker(nullptr);
1225 
1226  _handle.Release();
1227 
1228  if (_initialized)
1229  {
1230  Check(OCI_Cleanup());
1231  }
1232 
1233  _initialized = false;
1234 }

4229

4231 
4232  Check(OCI_CollToText(*this, &len, buffer));
4233

4235  }

4237  return OCI_STRING_NULL;
4238 }

4597 template<class T>
4598 void BindArray::BindArrayObject<T>::SetInData()
4599 {
4600  typename ObjectVector::iterator it, it_end;
4601 
4602  unsigned int index = 0;
4603  unsigned int currElemCount = Check(OCI_BindArrayGetSize(_pStatement));
4604 
4605  for (it = _vector.begin(), it_end = _vector.end(); it != it_end && index < _elemCount && index < currElemCount; ++it, ++index)
4606  {
4607  _data[index] = static_cast<NativeType>(*it);
4608  }
4609 }
4610 
4611 template<>
4612 inline void BindArray::BindArrayObject<ostring>::SetInData()
4613 {
4614  std::vector<ostring>::iterator it, it_end;
4615 
4616  unsigned int index = 0;
4617  unsigned int currElemCount = Check(OCI_BindArrayGetSize(_pStatement));
4618 
4619  for (it = _vector.begin(), it_end = _vector.end(); it != it_end && index < _elemCount && index < currElemCount; ++it, ++index)
4620  {
4621  const ostring & value = *it;
4622 
4623  memcpy( _data + (_elemSize * index), value.c_str(), (value.size() + 1) * sizeof(otext));
4624  }
4625 }
4626 
4627 template<>
4628 inline void BindArray::BindArrayObject<Raw>::SetInData()
4629 {
4630  std::vector<Raw>::iterator it, it_end;
4631 
4632  unsigned int index = 0;
4633  unsigned int currElemCount = Check(OCI_BindArrayGetSize(_pStatement));
4634 
4635  for (it = _vector.begin(), it_end = _vector.end(); it != it_end && index < _elemCount && index < currElemCount; ++it, ++index)
4636  {
4637  Raw & value = *it;
4638 
4639  if (value.size() > 0)
4640  {
4641  memcpy(_data + (_elemSize * index), &value[0], value.size());
4642  }
4643 
4644  OCI_BindSetDataSizeAtPos(OCI_GetBind2(_pStatement, GetName().c_str()), index + 1, static_cast<unsigned int>(value.size()));
4645  }
4646 }
4647 
4648 template<class T>
4649 void BindArray::BindArrayObject<T>::SetOutData()
4650 {
4651  typename ObjectVector::iterator it, it_end;
4652 
4653  unsigned int index = 0;
4654  unsigned int currElemCount = Check(OCI_BindArrayGetSize(_pStatement));
4655 
4656  for (it = _vector.begin(), it_end = _vector.end(); it != it_end && index < _elemCount && index < currElemCount; ++it, ++index)
4657  {
4658  T& object = *it;
4659 
4660  object = static_cast<NativeType>(_data[index]);
4661  }
4662 }
4663 
4664 template<>
4665 inline void BindArray::BindArrayObject<Raw>::SetOutData()
4666 {
4667  std::vector<Raw>::iterator it, it_end;
4668 
4669  OCI_Bind *pBind = Check(OCI_GetBind2(_pStatement, GetName().c_str()));
4670 
4671  unsigned int index = 0;
4672  unsigned int currElemCount = Check(OCI_BindArrayGetSize(_pStatement));
4673 
4674  for (it = _vector.begin(), it_end = _vector.end(); it != it_end && index < _elemCount && index < currElemCount; ++it, ++index)
4675  {
4676  unsigned char *currData = _data + (_elemSize * index);
4677 
4678  (*it).assign(currData, currData + Check(OCI_BindGetDataSizeAtPos(pBind, index + 1)));
4679  }
4680 }

4702  * --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

4704 template<class T>
4705 void BindObjectAdaptor<T>::SetInData()
4706 {
4707  if (GetMode() & OCI_BDM_IN)
4708  {
4709  size_t size = _object.size();
4710 
4711  if (size > _size)
4712  {
4713  size = _size;
4714  }
4715 
4716  if (size > 0)
4717  {
4718  memcpy(_data, &_object[0], size * sizeof(NativeType));
4719  }
4720 
4721  _data[size] = 0;
4722  }
4723 }
4724 
4725 template<class T>
4726 void BindObjectAdaptor<T>::SetOutData()
4727 {
4728  if (GetMode() & OCI_BDM_OUT)
4729  {
4730  size_t size = Check(OCI_BindGetDataSize(Check(OCI_GetBind2(_pStatement, _name.c_str()))));
4731 
4732  _object.assign(_data, _data + size);
4733  }
4734 }

4740  _data(new NativeType[size]),
4741  _size(size)

4743  memset(_data, 0, _size * sizeof(NativeType));

4833 inline void BindsHolder::Clear()
4834 {
4835  std::vector<BindObject *>::iterator it, it_end;
4836 
4837  for(it = _bindObjects.begin(), it_end = _bindObjects.end(); it != it_end; ++it)
4838  {
4839  delete (*it);
4840  }
4841 
4842  _bindObjects.clear();
4843 }
4844 
4845 inline void BindsHolder::AddBindObject(BindObject *bindObject)
4846 {
4847  if (Check(OCI_IsRebindingAllowed(_pStatement)))
4848  {
4849  std::vector<BindObject *>::iterator it, it_end;
4850 
4851  for(it = _bindObjects.begin(), it_end = _bindObjects.end(); it != it_end; ++it)
4852  {
4853  if ((*it)->GetName() == bindObject->GetName())
4854  {
4855  _bindObjects.erase(it);
4856  break;
4857  }
4858  }
4859  }
4860 
4861  _bindObjects.push_back(bindObject);
4862 }

4870  (*it)->SetOutData();
4871  }

5036 template<typename T>
5037 unsigned int Statement::Fetch(T callback)
5038 {
5039  unsigned int res = 0;
5040 
5041  Resultset rs = GetResultset();
5042 
5043  while (rs)
5044  {
5045  res += rs.ForEach(callback);
5046  rs = GetNextResultset();
5047  }
5048 
5049  return res;
5050 }
5051

5054 {
5055  unsigned int res = 0;
5056 
5057  Resultset rs = GetResultset();
5058 
5059  while (rs)
5060  {
5061  res += rs.ForEach(callback, adapter);
5062  rs = GetNextResultset();
5063  }
5064 
5065  return res;
5066 }

5142 template<typename M, class T>
5143 void Statement::BindVector1(M &method, const ostring& name, std::vector<T> &values, BindInfo::BindDirection mode)
5144 {
5145  BindArray * bnd = new BindArray(*this, name, mode);
5146  bnd->SetVector<T>(values, sizeof(typename BindResolver<T>::OutputType));
5147 
5148  boolean res = method(*this, name.c_str(), bnd->GetData<T>(), 0);
5149 
5150  if (res)
5151  {
5152  BindsHolder *bindsHolder = GetBindsHolder(true);
5153  bindsHolder->AddBindObject(bnd);
5154  SetLastBindMode(mode);
5155  }
5156  else
5157  {
5158  delete bnd;
5159  }
5160 
5161  Check(res);
5162 }

5548 template<>
5549 inline void Statement::Bind<ostring, unsigned int>(const ostring& name, std::vector<ostring> &values, unsigned int maxSize, BindInfo::BindDirection mode)
5550 {
5551  BindArray * bnd = new BindArray(*this, name, mode);
5552  bnd->SetVector<ostring>(values, maxSize+1);
5553 
5554  boolean res = OCI_BindArrayOfStrings(*this, name.c_str(), bnd->GetData<ostring>(), maxSize, 0);
5555 
5556  if (res)
5557  {
5558  BindsHolder *bindsHolder = GetBindsHolder(true);
5559  bindsHolder->AddBindObject(bnd);
5560  SetLastBindMode(mode);
5561  }
5562  else
5563  {
5564  delete bnd;
5565  }
5566 
5567  Check(res);
5568 }

5882 inline void Statement::ReleaseResultsets() const
5883 {
5884  if (_smartHandle)
5885  {
5886  Handle *handle = nullptr;
5887 
5888  while (_smartHandle->GetChildren().FindIf(IsResultsetHandle, handle))
5889  {
5890  if (handle)
5891  {
5892  handle->DetachFromHolders();
5893 
5894  delete handle;
5895 
5896  handle = nullptr;
5897  }
5898  }
5899  }
5900 }
5901 
5902 inline bool Statement::IsResultsetHandle(Handle *handle)
5903 {
5904  Resultset::SmartHandle *smartHandle = dynamic_cast<Resultset::SmartHandle *>(handle);
5905 
5906  return smartHandle != nullptr;
5907 }
5908 
5909 inline void Statement::OnFreeSmartHandle(SmartHandle *smartHandle)
5910 {
5911  if (smartHandle)
5912  {
5913  BindsHolder *bindsHolder = static_cast<BindsHolder *>(smartHandle->GetExtraInfos());
5914 
5915  smartHandle->SetExtraInfos(nullptr);
5916 
5917  delete bindsHolder;
5918  }
5919 }

5921 inline void Statement::SetLastBindMode(BindInfo::BindDirection mode)
5922 {
5923  Check(OCI_BindSetDirection(Check(OCI_GetBind(*this, Check(OCI_GetBindCount(*this)))), mode));
5924 }
5925 
5926 inline BindsHolder * Statement::GetBindsHolder(bool create) const
5927 {
5928  BindsHolder * bindsHolder = static_cast<BindsHolder *>(_smartHandle->GetExtraInfos());
5929 
5930  if (bindsHolder == nullptr && create)
5931  {
5932  bindsHolder = new BindsHolder(*this);
5933  _smartHandle->SetExtraInfos(bindsHolder);
5934  }
5935 
5936  return bindsHolder;
5937 }

6056 template<class TCallback>

6058 {

6060  {
6061  if (!callback(static_cast<const Resultset&>(*this)))
6062  {
6063  break;
6064  }
6065  }
6066 
6067  return GetCurrentRow();
6068 }

6074  {
6075  if (!callback(adapter(static_cast<const Resultset&>(*this))))
6076  {
6077  break;
6078  }
6079  }
6080 
6081  return GetCurrentRow();
6082 }

6497  reinterpret_cast<HandleFreeFunc>(OCI_SubscriptionUnregister), nullptr, nullptr);
6498 
6499  Environment::SetUserCallback<Subscription::NotifyHandlerProc>(static_cast<OCI_Subscription*>(*this), handler);
6500 }

6776 inline void Message::SetConsumers(std::vector<Agent> &agents)
6777 {
6778  size_t size = agents.size();
6779  ManagedBuffer<OCI_Agent*> buffer(size);
6780 
6781  OCI_Agent ** pAgents = static_cast<OCI_Agent **>(buffer);
6782 
6783  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
6784  {
6785  pAgents[i] = static_cast<const Agent &>(agents[i]);
6786  }
6787 
6788  Check(OCI_MsgSetConsumers(*this, pAgents, static_cast<unsigned int>(size)));
6789 }

6832 
6833  return MakeRaw(buffer, size);
6834 }

6955 inline void Dequeue::SetAgents(std::vector<Agent> &agents)
6956 {
6957  size_t size = agents.size();
6958  ManagedBuffer<OCI_Agent*> buffer(size);
6959 
6960  OCI_Agent ** pAgents = static_cast<OCI_Agent **>(buffer);
6961 
6962  for (size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
6963  {
6964  pAgents[i] = static_cast<const Agent &>(agents[i]);
6965  }
6966 
6967  Check(OCI_DequeueSetAgentList(*this, pAgents, static_cast<unsigned int>(size)));
6968 }
